      "writtenOn": "2017-11-14T20:22:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sort of, this uses jQuery\u0027s own selector system which was based off of CSS selectors.  This is to avoid implementing .find() to keep things simple.\n\nAdded $.escapeSelector() to escape selectors.\n\nI changed this not to use regex filtering, but to just divide the search query into individual words and matching on if all words are substrings. (eg \"cast linux\" will match \"linux chromium cast\" because it contains both of the words).  I think this is closer to what a user would expect.  We can revisit regex matching if someone asks for it in the future.",
      "parentUuid": "4da8a076_2ef3d69c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 38,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 38,
        "endChar": 37
